column14: Good quality ADCP measurement, to be used for curve development.  Arrived to find mud in and around gauge house, N2 tank and flushing equipment knocked over inside. Power still active in GH (light on), but battery charger not responding. Both sensors (Accubar & shaft enc) reporting error, suspect logger was zapped in some way. Appears to still be functioning aside from SDI issues. Correct time, not obvious warnings/issues. D/L data & programming then power cycled logger @ 1007 MST. Attempted to remap SDI sensors, but they could not be found. Unplugged shaft encoder as its no longer being used. Replaced SDI cable to accubar, attempted to map again, still no response. Swapped logger @ 1036 MST. No change. Installed Ott on 25lb plate weight tossed into gauge pool as a temporary measure (did not have spare accubar). Sitting appx 1.36m deep. Confirmed reading in m, deg C, 20s averaging set in sensor. HG going down during maintenance, but going up during MMT - left rod in water for multiple cuts. ADCP by Moving Boat
